Because the logic behind it is not to discuss "whether poetry can be allowed to stay in the face of disaster" , but to treat poetry directly as a non-daily existence, as if feeling the wind and singing the moon are all special emotional rituals, and it is not easy to give them out at will on weekdays, the logic that the poet has to wave a fan to become a poet excludes poetry from life, but poetry is supposed to be everyday.

I find the idea that poetry needs to be decided more frightening than the idea that it is uncultured.
Compared to the uncultured thing, I think it's scariest to be struck by just a few lines of poetry, because it says, our lives are so far from poetry.

These days, some media said "the same day, " as "Wuhan refueling, " after the crowd jeered. Because the logic behind it is not to discuss "whether poetry can be allowed to stay in the face of disaster" , but to treat poetry directly as a non-daily existence, as if feeling the wind and singing the moon are all special emotional rituals, and it is not easy to give them out at will on weekdays, the logic that the poet has to wave a fan to become a poet excludes poetry from life, but poetry is supposed to be everyday.

Everywhere under the blockade, I have the idea person, is separated in the distant countryside;

And I returned for it a beautiful Ju-gem ;

And lonely birds have sung their grief.

When a line of poetry, a word flash in the heart, we seem to be separated by thousands of years and the hearts of the old people, sad to tell each other. But some people think that writing poetry is too artsy for serious anti-epidemic action..

I find the idea that poetry needs to be decided more frightening than the idea that it is uncultured.

Compared to the uncultured thing, I think it's scariest to be struck by just a few lines of poetry, because it says, our lives are so far from poetry.

When I think of a popular question and answer session I once saw, I am impressed:

"Why do we read poetry? "

"To grow up and face the beauty of the Buddhist cosmology, the image that comes to mind is not 'I X' and 'Niu B' , but 'sunset clouds and lone ducks fly together, autumn waters grow in one color. ' "

Quote:

Male, born in 1969, now living in Wuhan. He is the author of the Poetry Anthology China Standard Time and the improvisation. The collection of essays "the province of sorrow" , "All the silence of the world is here now. ".

Dictation

Tidying up, Abu

We have other ways of saying it

I'm in Wuhan. It's Day twenty-two.

These two days, because the Japanese friend donates the matter which the aid China, makes the boiling noise. Interestingly, the focus of public opinion field is not material problems, but the packaging box on a few lines of Tang poetry. According to the usual idea, this is similar to the next door to see you sick, home to send a basket of flowers, fruit, while writing a prayer note, above wrote a few words of courtesy. In accordance with the traditional Chinese custom, reciprocity, should be good smoke good tea to entertain.

What made those touching poems appear on the Japanese Aid to China? In my opinion, it is simply because, in the face of disaster, the Japanese feel that China should still be that China.

I also in the friend circle, expressed to see a few lines of Tang poetry on a swarm of surprise inexplicable dissatisfaction. Many people reply, mostly talking about China and Japan's cultural heritage, development and differences. One of the best responses was from Cao Cao, a writer in Nanjing: "The problem is, I don't think quoting poetry is called culture. But maybe it's Ok to say that the Chinese are culturally literate, because they're amazed by a few lines of poetry. "

But it doesn't seem that simple.

Reciting a few lines of Tang poetry doesn't mean who has culture or who doesn't, but it does remind us of other ways of expression, other modes of emotion, and other ways of thinking that aren't wrapped up in this very awkward time. That is another "different" world, it comes from the Han, Tang, song and Yuan Dynasties, from the magnificent moon, from the surging river, from the countless treasures of Chinese civilization, more than four or six simple sentences?

It's been twenty-two long days since the city was shut down, and each of our lives have changed dramatically. We have seen so much misfortune that it seems that we can no longer live as we used to. That is a common problem that plagues us all.

It is not barbarous to write poetry after a calamity; it is barbarous to continue it with shameless speech. And the only way to resist this savagery is to write truly, consistently and firmly, so that the lie dies and the truth comes out, so that the sun shines through the haze and relights the parched gardens, the lonely world.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
After the Wuhan outbreak, Kohiki has been collecting portraits of "Chinese poets in masks, " some of which he has collected. When poets wear masks, do you recognize them?

Humanity can only surrender for so long

The city closed for more than 20 days, a bit like a prisoner, and finally put the schedule completely reversed. Especially in the last week, has been able to stay up all night, until 5:00 in the morning before sleep. Sleep until noon, Wuhan called "sleep turn the clock. ". I did not feel faint, but a strange feeling, this is the new year, but also refuge, open my eyes to see, the weather outside the window is no more than three: Sunny, rainy and cloudy days.

I live in a community of four, each 30-story, each basically have a few confirmed patients, protection of privacy did not publish house number, residents are mostly closed doors, do not go out.

The community is surrounded by three universities, usually always students come and go to the lively, suddenly become so quiet, it feels quite strange. I never imagined that a city of ten million people would suddenly become invisible -- as if I were standing on my balcony looking out, feeling strange and unreal, but true.

Daily meals are still a big drain. The nearby 24-hour convenience stores and large business circles are closed, but the supermarkets are still open. The box-horse and wu-shang supermarkets in Wuhan have relatively high coverage, you can easily buy fruits, vegetables, meat, eggs and supplies.

Say A PARAGRAPH OF WUHAN DIALECT: In the alipay to find the purchase, to buy eggs, rice, oil, order, a few minutes to take the person. $10 for the bird. re-order. This is fast. Pick Up. To the downstairs to receive the delivery boy sent on behalf of the purchase of goods, really increased money, good service, fast. Don't behave, a few dollars, packed in good condition, I'm afraid you infected, with a plastic bag to hand over. Community Gate Station to the checkout, we two people wear masks, two meters apart, next to a chemical-resistant clothing property, calmly took the temperature gun aimed at us. I feel like I'm in the police station for something.

More than 20 days in addition to go out to buy food, all day wearing long johns in the study around. It's not hot enough to keep the floor warm at 50 degrees, and the virus is said to dread it -- why else would it disappear in May and June? This is speculation, of course, and there is no scientific basis for confirmation. During Wuhan's cold and humid winter, 9 million people shut themselves off for more than 20 days, verging on a great performance art. But just to be clear, not all of us are self-contained, highly contagious diseases, that allow the boundaries between initiative and passivity to disappear at this moment, which is actually submission, and human beings should be humble in the face of a virus.

Wuhan is like a computer shutdown now

People in Wuhan have always been bold, and at the beginning of January this year, they didn't care. There were official banquets for 10,000 people, and there were Mass New Year celebrations in closed venues all over the city. After the news of Dr. Li Wenliang came out, all kinds of news were flying around among the people. People would remind each other, but because there was no official certification, life did not change.

A few days before the city closed down, I was having dinner with a friend. A friend, a doctor, told us the next day that something had happened. One of his colleagues had a fever and was waiting for the test results, "If he's infected, I'm quarantined, you're in danger. " We wait with him until 8:00, say it's over, the virus is off -- it's not a death sentence, but it's a constant threat, it makes you feel so close to death. It's psychological stress for everyone who isn't infected. It's subtle.

I originally planned to go to Tibet for the Spring Festival this year. I had booked my ticket half a month in advance, but I returned the ticket after the announcement. Soon after the announcement, Wuhan closed the city of Foshan, making me feel that this was an unusual situation, looks like another SARS outbreak. But Wuhan People's memory of SARS is not strong. When the city was closed at the beginning, it was the most frightening time for everyone. Now, more than 20 days later, it has become a bit numb. Nine million people don't go out and don't go out. The virus has changed the rhythm of our daily lives, reduced to living, feeding, and getting enough sleep.

I've been wondering: After the virus has passed, will we be able to live as recklessly as before? And it's not just about not being in the wild. Super-sized cities like Wuhan, coupled with faster and faster inter-city transport networks, have also taken high-speed rail to places previously inaccessible. Super-large cities to the surrounding workers unlimited absorption, when disaster will directly into the virus to breathe in. This reminds me of the early years of the 386 computer, if there is no way to poisoning had to power down, shutdown. Wuhan is like a computer shutdown now, but we can't keep doing this forever, killing 10,000 enemies to lose 3,000.

This virus is not only a problem for medicine and technology, but also a new problem for the social structure of modern civilization —— How to defend the rapidly developing city in layers? This is also the question facing sociology: How do we construct the social structure more scientifically?

Then I'll have to square dance

There are a lot of free-spirited people in my circle of friends, and I am one of them. When I say "untrammeled, " I mean something concrete, something more personal. For example, yesterday morning, old Chen of art workshop No. 5 took to the street alone and filmed the empty street. He said as he filmed, there are 10 million ambush troops here. I teased him by saying, Chen, you are a straw boat, and now you can finally go with the tide. Chen replied, I am the fog, you are the stack, old Fang is the straw boat. The Lao Fang he was talking about was Fang Wen, the owner of the Zheming Bar. When the epidemic was at its worst, he went alone to the riverbank to play football. The Sun was shining, the sky was clear, and the weather was so good that it made people a little uneasy, fang Wen in the Empty Beach Exclamation: This is really a fucking waste Ah!

A friend of mine works at the police station, and the shelter has just been built, and we need to move all the minor patients in the communities. His precinct moved about 40 or 50 people, all kinds of mental work, luggage, formalities, pick-ups and so on. I finally got the guy to the Wembley Arena, went back to the clinic to prepare dinner, and then I got a call that two of your guys had run off.

My friend couldn't get back in the saddle, track down the missing infectees, and end up clogging the house, asking, "why did you run home when you got infected in the shelter? "? TAT, it's too noisy there, I can't sleep. Ask, aren't you afraid of infecting your family when you come back? A, they all welcome me back... a whole day, 18 hours, more than a dozen people in the work of the staff in the transfer.

I'm just telling the story, absurdly true, in a simplified version of One Flew Over the CUCKOO's Nest. A man like Mike Murphy, if you threw him in a shelter, would also demand that there be a bar room in the shelter where our drinking buddies could be together, look after each other, and recover more quickly. If the nurses object, Mike Murphy would say, then I'll have to square dance.

The Fly magically disappeared

In the afternoon, he sneaked down the stairs and went for a turn. The garden was quiet, not even a fly. I found this problem a few days ago, since the outbreak of Wuhan, the flies magically disappeared. I don't know. has anyone else in Hanyang, Hankou, noticed?

Standing by the Dry Fountain Smoking, this Byzantine Roman taste, coupled with chinese-style rockery, no water flow through, looks shabby, narrow, lifeless. A friend of mine in the building next door had a long conversation with me at noon. I guess he wanted to meet me downstairs in the flower bed for a smoke. I kept my mouth shut and thought to myself, two trapped in the same neighborhood "Mike Murphy" should not meet, we can be like Yu Zecheng, passing by seems not to know, underground party should be the rules. Otherwise, every day a stew hot pot, Mao shop wine opened, where a little epidemic area of the People's appearance.

The brother in the building next door seems to be unrelenting, and he sent me a message on Weixin ——"every afternoon and evening, Xiao Wu and I walk around the community, stretch our legs... " this is the standard language of a lurker, here's the code word. But I was having dinner, did not have time to return, I think, is to go down to exchange information with him, also do not know his family's supplies are sufficient.

Actually, I had to take a trip today. GROMIT says he's out of masks. There's only two left. I happen to have Zhejiang poet Jin Du and two other friends sent masks, I said you just come over box Ma Sheng fresh shopping replenishment, I sent with you. At three o'clock, Gao was waiting for me in the open road. I thought since I was out of the House, I might as well go shopping with him? Although there seems to be no shortage of things at home.

Past the Bar Street at the back door of Huashi, it had been empty for a month. Craft Beer, Lamb Scorpions, skewers of incense, northeast dumpling restaurant, braised chicken and rice... I remember that every boss is quite lovely, I am familiar with it, this can be discounted, that can be discounted, I am a little worried that this epidemic is too long, i'm afraid a lot of them won't be coming back.

Two people walk to box horse, met a group of young people riding bicycles in the street to reach, I said, now the children are really bold. A girl riding in the back, back to me, we have no food to eat! Ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha.

Lost for decades, brothers can be reunited

The poet, Missing, posted an online message in the afternoon saying that his uncle had met in Wuhan in the early 1990s and had not been heard from in 26 years. The epidemic in Wuhan shook the country, Liu Buwei's father when he was old, miss his brother, asked not Wei Internet search.

I sent the message to the Group of students, did not expect the day, unexpectedly quickly received a response. His uncle and my classmate's father turned out to be a unit, and very close personal friends, got this message, tears of joy.

It is said that any stranger in the world need only turn three corners to find another person. It seems true.

Buwei told me privately that his father was studying in Liaoyang at the beginning of liberation, and his uncle went to study in Changchun. Later, when his brother was separated, they went their separate ways, and when things changed, no one dared contact the other easily. There was one contact in the late'70s, another in the early'90s, and then nothing.

I understand the personal destiny of that era, as the wind blows the dust, sprinkle the earth. In the twilight of his life, everyone will miss his hometown and relatives. Spring in Anshan, summer in Shenyang, Liu Buwei describes his father's generation to me wistfully, like a slow motion scene in an old movie, beautiful and sad.

It was a warm scene from the bleak and ICY Wuhan epidemic. How shall it be said that you have no clothes ? I will share my lower garments with you . The Ynagtze flows east.
